      "acceptanceCriteria": "Solver convergence to manufactured solutions demonstrated for relevant governing equations (incompressible Navier-Stokes with rotating reference frame).",
      "rationale": "Method of manufactured solutions applied to rotating-frame incompressible flow benchmark. Second-order spatial convergence confirmed. Code verification documentation on file."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Discretization error",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Grid convergence index (GCI) for NIH QOI shall be less than 10% across the operating envelope.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed (coarse 2.1M, medium 5.8M, fine 14.2M elements). GCI for NIH ranged from 3.1% to 7.4% across all five operating points, satisfying the 10% threshold. Fine mesh adopted for all production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation must replicate at least three of the five CFD operating points within ±5% of target flow rate and rotational speed.",
      "rationale": "FDA pump benchmark experiments conducted at matching flow rates (2, 4, 6 L/min) and rotational speeds (2000, 2500, 3500 RPM). Four of five operating points replicated within ±3%. Blood analog fluid properties matched to within ±2% of CFD input values."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Output comparison",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted NIH values must agree with experimental measurements within 15% mean relative error across validated operating points.",
      "rationale": "Mean relative error between CFD-predicted NIH and experimental NIH was 8.3% across four validated operating points. Maximum single-point error was 12.7%. Both metrics satisfy the 15% acceptance criterion. Systematic underprediction at high rotational speed noted but within tolerance."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "The primary QOI (NIH and derived RH) must be directly linked to the clinical risk metric (hemolysis-related adverse events) through a documented mechanistic or empirical pathway.",
      "rationale": "NIH is an ISO 10993-compliant hemolysis metric directly correlated with plasma free hemoglobin elevation. RH as a ratio normalizes device-to-device comparison consistent with FDA guidance on predicate comparisons. QOI relevance chain fully documented in design dossier."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the validation activities to the COU",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Validation activities must use the same pump geometry family and overlapping operating conditions as the COU, with blood analog fluid properties representative of clinical CPB conditions.",
      "rationale": "Validation performed on FDA generic centrifugal pump geometry — same impeller topology as candidate device. Operating conditions span the CPB clinical range (2–6 L/min, 2000–3500 RPM). Glycerol-water blood analog (viscosity 3.5 cP) used, matching clinical blood viscosity. Relevance to COU confirmed."
    },
